ZH: 他总是看不起别人的意见。
EN: He always looks down on others' opinions.

ZH: 她很自负，总是看不起别人。
EN: She is very arrogant and always looks down on others.

ZH: 他们看不起那个穷人。
EN: They look down on that poor man.

ZH: 你不应该看不起她，她是个好人。
EN: You shouldn't look down on her, she is a good person.

ZH: 我们不要看不起劳动者。
EN: We should not look down on laborers.

ZH: 孩子们不应该看不起老师。
EN: Children should not look down on teachers.

ZH: 他的做法让人看不起。
EN: His behavior is contemptible.

ZH: 这种态度不值得看不起。
EN: This kind of attitude is not worthy of contempt.

ZH: 老板总是看不起底层员工。
EN: The boss always looks down on the lower-level employees.

ZH: 这种态度让她看不起你。
EN: This attitude makes her look down on you.

ZH: 他看不起那些没有教育的人。
EN: He looks down on those without education.

ZH: 我们不应该看不起弱势群体。
EN: We should not look down on vulnerable groups.

ZH: 他想通过看不起别人来证明自己的优越感。
EN: He wants to prove his superiority by looking down on others.

ZH: 那些领导总是看不起下属。
EN: Those leaders always look down on their subordinates.

ZH: 我们看不起那种势利的行为。
EN: We look down on that kind of snobbish behavior.

ZH: 这么做只会让人看不起你。
EN: Doing this will only make people look down on you.

ZH: 他总是看不起那些不如他的人。
EN: He always looks down on people who are not as good as him.

ZH: 不要看不起别人，因为每个人都有自己的优点。
EN: Don't look down on others, because everyone has their own strengths.

ZH: 他的言行举止始终让人看不起。
EN: His words and actions always make people look down on him.

ZH: 看不起他人说明你自己没有多大本事。
EN: Looking down on others shows that you are not that great yourself.
